attributes.Long form description: The student is to disassemble the rolling cart. The student turns over the rolling cart and starts to disassemble the wheels. Next, the student unscrews the hexagon cap nut from the screws and brackets and removes the trays. Then the student disassembles the bar and the base frame. Lastly, the student put them together on the table neatly.

attributes.Transcription: Ok now we're going to disassemble this furniture.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first two wheels from the base of the rolling cart.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should put the utility cart 90° down when he start to disassemble it.

attributes.Transcription: To start, you should, ah, put it 90° down.
The wheels that are not on the table anymore.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should put the wheel outside of the table to have better access.

attributes.Transcription: You should put the wheel outside of the table to have better access.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the bottom wheels from the base frame of the rolling cart.
The student detaches the top tray of the rolling cart.
The student detaches the middle tray of the rolling cart.
The student detaches the bottom tray of the rolling cart.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should put the utility cart stand up again to remove the last bracket.

attributes.Transcription: You should put the furniture stand up again to remove the last bracket.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the screws of the bars from the base frame.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should start by removing the lower parts.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the screws of the bars from the base frame.
The student disassembles the base frame that is bent.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student attempts to detach the base frame by rotating it, however this is incorrect because you cannot detach the base frames both at the same time.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the screws in the middle of the bars with a screwdriver.
The student disassembles the bars and places them in the trays.
